Dialogue: 0,00:08:09.300,00:08:12.480,辉英,,0,0,0,,why is it important to take the maximum DFTU?
Dialogue: 0,00:08:14.460,00:08:20.440,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is because, again, of the entropy condition.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:21.340,00:08:23.320,辉英,,0,0,0,,So remember, the entropy condition says that
Dialogue: 0,00:08:23.320,00:08:28.980,辉英,,0,0,0,,no characteristics can emerge from a discontinuity, right?
Dialogue: 0,00:08:30.200,00:08:36.740,辉英,,0,0,0,,And in this case, because we had a count example
Dialogue: 0,00:08:36.740,00:08:41.320,辉英,,0,0,0,,that doesn't satisfy the entropy condition in the Berger's equation.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:41.740,00:08:49.980,辉英,,0,0,0,,So if we have an inverted shock wave where on the left u is equal to minus 1,
Dialogue: 0,00:08:50.180,00:08:52.300,辉英,,0,0,0,,on the right u is equal to plus 1.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:53.220,00:09:01.340,辉英,,0,0,0,,What happens is that the flux on both left and right of the shock wave
Dialogue: 0,00:09:01.340,00:09:02.620,辉英,,0,0,0,,is going to be the same.
Dialogue: 0,00:09:03.520,00:09:06.320,辉英,,0,0,0,,So that is going to prevent DUT.
Dialogue: 0,00:09:06.740,00:09:08.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,DUT to change.
Dialogue: 0,00:09:08.620,00:09:14.740,辉英,,0,0,0,,That is, prevent u to change by this difference in the flux alone.
Dialogue: 0,00:09:17.060,00:09:20.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,What's going to, in this scheme, in this scheme,
Dialogue: 0,00:09:20.280,00:09:24.840,辉英,,0,0,0,,what is enforcing the entropy condition to be satisfied
Dialogue: 0,00:09:24.840,00:09:27.480,辉英,,0,0,0,,is actually this numerical dissipation here.
Dialogue: 0,00:09:28.600,00:09:31.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,And the numerical dissipation here,
Dialogue: 0,00:09:31.560,00:09:34.580,辉英,,0,0,0,,we need to take the maximum DFTU here
Dialogue: 0,00:09:34.580,00:09:36.720,辉英,,0,0,0,,in order for the numerical dissipation,
Dialogue: 0,00:09:36.740,00:09:40.420,辉英,,0,0,0,,to be sufficiently strong to satisfy the entropy condition.
Dialogue: 0,00:09:41.600,00:09:43.900,辉英,,0,0,0,,All right, so for example, the grid point here
Dialogue: 0,00:09:43.900,00:09:46.780,辉英,,0,0,0,,is going to be pulled downwards.
Dialogue: 0,00:09:46.980,00:09:49.040,辉英,,0,0,0,,The grid point here is going to be pulled upwards
Dialogue: 0,00:09:49.040,00:09:50.740,辉英,,0,0,0,,by this numerical dissipation.
Dialogue: 0,00:09:53.520,00:09:54.740,辉英,,0,0,0,,Does that answer your question?
Dialogue: 0,00:09:55.020,00:09:55.200,辉英,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,00:09:56.260,00:09:58.300,辉英,,0,0,0,,So in a system of conservation loss,
Dialogue: 0,00:09:59.300,00:10:01.420,辉英,,0,0,0,,we can apply the same scheme.
Dialogue: 0,00:10:01.640,00:10:04.180,辉英,,0,0,0,,We can compute the flux as the average
Dialogue: 0,00:10:04.180,00:10:06.700,辉英,,0,0,0,,between the flux on the left and the flux on the right.
Dialogue: 0,00:10:06.740,00:10:13.480,辉英,,0,0,0,,Plus a delta x times the maximum of the absolute values
Dialogue: 0,00:10:13.480,00:10:16.140,辉英,,0,0,0,,of different characteristic speeds.
